# Vue template — test hooks (`data-test-*`)

Use this rule when adding or changing **attributes the UI tests locate**. It pairs with [playwright-tests.mdc](playwright-tests.mdc), which defines how `selectorList` and locators are written in `*.playwright.*.ts` files (including rare **full** selector strings in `selectorList` for portaled nodes that cannot carry project hooks, such as `'[role="tooltip"]'` for Quasar tooltips).

## Do not use bare `data-test`

- **Never** add `data-test="..."` on production templates. Use **`data-test-locator="..."`** (or `:data-test-locator`) for the primary stable id Playwright/Vitest select with `[data-test-locator="..."]`.
- Add **additional** hyphenated attributes only when tests need extra semantics (examples below).

## Primary locator

- **`data-test-locator`** — stable string id per node (often `componentName-role-suffix`, e.g. `dialogProgramSettings-title`, `globalWindowButtons-button-minimize`). Tests store these values in `selectorList` and build locators as `appWindow.locator(\`[data-test-locator="${selectorList.someKey}"]\`)`.

## Other `data-test-*` hooks in this repo

- **`data-test-setting-id`**, **`data-test-tags`**, **`data-test-tooltip-text`** on Program Settings rows and help icons ([DialogProgramSettings.vue](src/components/dialogs/DialogProgramSettings/DialogProgramSettings.vue)).
- **Menu bar**: **`data-test-menu-test`** and **`data-test-menu-any`** on [AppControlMenus.vue](src/components/globals/AppControlMenus/AppControlMenus.vue) (see [AppControlMenus.playwright.test.ts](src/components/globals/AppControlMenus/_tests/AppControlMenus.playwright.test.ts)); Playwright uses `[data-test-menu-test="..."]` / `[data-test-menu-any="..."]`.
- **Metadata / flags** asserted via attributes or `dataset`: e.g. **`data-test-image`**, **`data-test-is-random`**, **`data-test-layout-width`**, **`data-test-layout-height`** ([FantasiaMascotImage.vue](src/components/elements/FantasiaMascotImage/FantasiaMascotImage.vue)); the same layout keys on **[SocialContactSingleButton](src/components/elements/SocialContactSingleButton/SocialContactSingleButton.vue)** **q-img** and on the splash **SVG** in **[index.html](index.html)**; **`data-test-error-card-width`** on **[ErrorCard](src/components/elements/ErrorCard/ErrorCard.vue)** (max-width cap in CSS pixels). **`data-test-button-number`** ([SocialContactButtons.vue](src/components/other/SocialContactButtons/SocialContactButtons.vue)), **`data-test-has-proper-data-input`** ([AppControlSingleMenu.vue](src/components/globals/AppControlSingleMenu/AppControlSingleMenu.vue)).

## Naming

- Typically **lowerCamelCase block** plus hyphen-separated segments in the **value** of `data-test-locator`, e.g. `globalWindowButtons-button-minimize`, `dialogMarkdownDocument-markdown-wrapper`.
- Child components may use shorter or compound names consistent with that subtree (e.g. `socialContactSingleButton-image`).
- **Stay consistent** within the component and with the existing `selectorList` in its `_tests/*.playwright.test.ts` file.

## Workflow

1. Add or update hooks on the template (`data-test-locator` plus any extra `data-test-*` needed).
2. Update the component’s Playwright `selectorList` and tests to match ([playwright-tests.mdc](playwright-tests.mdc)); Vitest/Storybook queries use the same attribute names.
3. Rebuild before running Playwright ([README.md](README.md)).

## Not in this rule

- BEM **classes** for styling → [vue-bem-scss.mdc](vue-bem-scss.mdc).
- Quasar / Composition API / script extraction → [vue-quasar.mdc](vue-quasar.mdc).

## Local types extraction rule

- For Vue (`.vue`) and TypeScript (`.ts`) source files, move small file-local interfaces/type aliases into a colocated `<filename>.types.ts` file and import them back.
- For JavaScript (`.js`), TypeScript (`.ts`), Vue (`.vue`), and JSON (`.json`, `.jsonc`, `.json5`) files, enforce expanded multi-line object literals via ESLint (`object-curly-newline` + `object-property-newline`) and keep files auto-fixable with `eslint --fix`.
